1
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:12,400
Next.

2
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:17,440
Come on, next.

3
00:00:23,710 --> 00:00:24,550
Next.

4
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,790
Tang Tang, you're so skinny.

5
00:00:57,790 --> 00:00:59,280
Give me your food.

6
00:00:59,710 --> 00:01:00,790
That's Tang Tang's.

7
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:01,630
You...

8
00:01:17,790 --> 00:01:18,660
Thanks.

9
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:19,640
Run faster next time,

10
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,150
or you won't get any food.

11
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,560
What's that?

12
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,040
A birthmark.

13
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,510
What's a birthmark?

14
00:01:44,710 --> 00:01:47,590
A mark only I have.

15
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,920
Why don't I have one?

16
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,120
Not everyone does.

17
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,710
Yours is really pretty.

18
00:01:54,710 --> 00:01:55,760
It's like a little flower.

19
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:02,920
That's really high.

20
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:04,510
Looks fun.

21
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:06,950
My parents took me on it before.

22
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:09,680
From the top, you can see the whole city.

23
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,840
That's nice.

24
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,560
You had parents?

25
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:15,240
I've never seen mine.

26
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:19,470
You'll meet good people someday

27
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:20,520
to take you home.

28
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,080
You'll have a home too.

29
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:23,680
Can we go play?

30
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,560
You need tickets.

31
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:27,280
I don't have money.

32
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:28,630
Me neither.

33
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:31,910
When I grow up,

34
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,400
I'll take you on the Ferris wheel.

35
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,240
Deal?

36
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,960
Deal. I'll remember that.

37
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,360
Always.

38
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:55,060
=The Hidden Truth=

39
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:57,700
=Episode 5=

40
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:28,710
What's that?

41
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,080
A birthmark.

42
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:32,310
What's a birthmark?

43
00:03:33,710 --> 00:03:36,590
A mark only I have.

44
00:03:37,190 --> 00:03:38,710
Why don't I have one?

45
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,030
Not everyone does.

46
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,030
Yours is really pretty.

47
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,150
It's like a little flower.

48
00:03:47,870 --> 00:03:48,710
Tang Tang,

49
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:51,080
want to go somewhere fun?

50
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,560
Honestly,

51
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,000
I don't know why,

52
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,360
but I've forgotten

53
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:15,030
a lot from childhood.

54
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:43,500
(Incoming call: Tang Tang)

55
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:47,270
Ms. Tong?

56
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:50,270
Ms. Tong?

57
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:53,790
Ms. Tong?

58
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:01,060
Ms. Tong.

59
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:02,120
Yimo.

60
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:06,510
Your door's shut.

61
00:05:08,510 --> 00:05:09,510
Look at me.

62
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:12,270
It's fine. I have my keys.

63
00:05:13,630 --> 00:05:15,040
I made milk tea with grass jelly.

64
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:15,910
It's sweet.

65
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:16,800
You'll like it.

66
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,800
Open the door.

67
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,800
Let me bring it in.

68
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,800
No need. I'll take it myself.

69
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:22,240
It's fine. I'll help.

70
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,080
No need.

71
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,310
I mean,

72
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:27,510
I was cleaning.

73
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:28,390
It's a mess.

74
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,350
Give it to me.

75
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,320
Okay.

76
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,440
Hey,

77
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:37,000
didn't we say we'd go shopping?

78
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,090
Didn't get to last time.

79
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,680
You busy today?

80
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:41,560
Let's go out later.

81
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:42,470
Sure.

82
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:44,270
Then go back first.

83
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:46,000
I'll come get you when I'm done.

84
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,870
Okay, I'll wait.

85
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:54,560
See you in a bit.

86
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:56,470
Alright.

87
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:12,350
Ms. Tong.

88
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,120
This one looks good.

89
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:15,630
It'd suit you.

90
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:16,880
Let me see.

91
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,310
It's nice.

92
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,640
Yimo,

93
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,830
no wonder you studied design.

94
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,070
You have great taste.

95
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:25,310
Let me help you try it on.

96
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:26,600
No need.

97
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,630
It's fine.

98
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:35,230
Yimo,

99
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:37,070
I'll do it myself.

100
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,520
Okay.

101
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,560
Hey,

102
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,480
your dad told me

103
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,120
about what happened at the station.

104
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,680
He really laid into me.

105
00:06:57,870 --> 00:07:00,000
I know you were saving your friend.

106
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,270
I understand.

107
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:04,310
But you're his only daughter.

108
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,800
If something happened to you,

109
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:06,830
what would he do?

110
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,560
It was my fault.

111
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:10,390
I never thought

112
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:11,870
things would get that far.

113
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,190
How did you know those people

114
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:18,160
at the teahouse?

115
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,800
I didn't know them.

116
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,950
I had no choice.

117
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,390
I didn't dare to tell my dad.

118
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,120
So I asked a classmate.

119
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,750
Turns out he's so unreliable.

120
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:35,470
Listen.

121
00:07:35,820 --> 00:07:36,680
From now on,

122
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,430
if there's anything you can't tell your dad,

123
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,830
just tell me.

124
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,720
At least you'll have someone to talk to.

125
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:43,870
Besides,

126
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:45,750
your dad's a grown man.

127
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,390
Men think differently

128
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:48,510
from us sometimes.

129
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,030
Okay.

130
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:55,470
Here.

131
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,080
Tang, not just you.

132
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:01,920
Whenever your friends

133
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:02,950
or coworkers come by,

134
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:03,830
just let me know.

135
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:05,390
It's on the house.

136
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,840
Thank you.

137
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:16,630
You and Yimo are close, right?

138
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:17,880
Not really.

139
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:20,920
In the dog theft case,

140
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,630
Yimo stepped in to help.

141
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,040
That was the first time we met.

142
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:30,000
Do detectives handle dog theft too?

143
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,270
Of course.

144
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:32,600
Big or small,

145
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,960
it's our job.

146
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,680
Well,

147
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:43,670
she's my only child.

148
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,390
Here's to you.

149
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,230
Thanks.

150
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:49,320
You're a good guy.

151
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,550
Hold on, sir.

152
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,480
I can't drink this yet.

153
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:01,600
I think you misunderstood.

154
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,870
Yimo and I are just friends.

155
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:07,150
That's it.

156
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:08,750
You're making me feel

157
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,030
kind of embarrassed.

158
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:11,480
I really think

159
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,960
you're a good guy.

160
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,440
What do you think of Yimo?

161
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,000
She's great.

162
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,600
Kind and warm.

163
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:23,360
Honestly,

164
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:25,390
when I first met her,

165
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:26,870
it feels like

166
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,480
she's familiar.

167
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,200
It's like

168
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:34,150
we knew each other as kids.

169
00:09:35,390 --> 00:09:36,790
But she said

170
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,870
she doesn't remember anything
from back then.

171
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,150
Ms. Tong.

172
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,000
What's that scar from?

173
00:09:57,910 --> 00:09:58,840
Oh, that?

174
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,750
An old accident

175
00:10:00,750 --> 00:10:01,750
back home.

176
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:05,630
Did it scare you?

177
00:10:08,390 --> 00:10:10,320
There's a dermatologist
at Third City Hospital.

178
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,960
Great with scar removal.

179
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,200
My friend Xiaoqian

180
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,750
had a scar on her forehead.

181
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:16,120
She got it removed.

182
00:10:16,510 --> 00:10:18,080
Now you can't even tell.

183
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:20,600
If you want, I'll go with you.

184
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,440
I'm used to it.

185
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,080
Besides,

186
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:27,510
it's on my back.

187
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:29,000
I barely see

188
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,120
or think about it.

189
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:32,270
If you ever change your mind,

190
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,200
tell me.

191
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:34,470
Okay.

192
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:36,870
Ms. Tong,

193
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,440
where's your hometown?

194
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,870
I'm from Shancheng.

195
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,550
I thought so.

196
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:50,360
Your accent sounded like it.

197
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,150
Not many people from there here.

198
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:53,200
It's pretty rare.

199
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,000
Funny thing is,

200
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:57,120
everyone I've met from there is really nice.

201
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,630
I've never visited though.

202
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:02,630
There's nothing to see.

203
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,750
You'd regret it.

204
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:05,750
Sir,

205
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,360
did something happen to Yimo

206
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:09,960
when she was little?

207
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,390
I mean, when I mentioned

208
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:13,990
the welfare home,

209
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,320
and being adopted,

210
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,480
she said she can't remember a thing.

211
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,910
Yimo is my daughter.

212
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:33,750
That won't change

213
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:36,200
no matter what.

214
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,790
Don't take this wrong, sir.

215
00:11:44,630 --> 00:11:46,030
I just want to look out for her.

216
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,150
Cheers, sir.

217
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,200
So Ms. Tong,

218
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:54,510
how did you meet my dad?

219
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,510
I asked him,

220
00:11:56,630 --> 00:11:57,960
but he won't say.

221
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,510
I had a ton of luggage

222
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:02,720
when I moved in,

223
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,600
but the movers

224
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:06,360
dumped them in the hallway.

225
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:10,320
Said carrying it inside cost extra.

226
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,790
Can you believe that?

227
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:13,600
And then,

228
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,550
your dad came home

229
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:15,750
and got blocked.

230
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:16,960
In the end,

231
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,360
he carried everything in for me,

232
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,480
piece by piece.

233
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,030
Seriously?

234
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,750
He hates chores.

235
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:24,750
Right?

236
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:25,960
He was exhausted.

237
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,390
So I thought,

238
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,000
I couldn't just ignore that.

239
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,600
Since then,

240
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,550
I've been baking

241
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:34,870
for him.

242
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,750
Day by day,

243
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,120
we got familiar.

244
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,110
What?

245
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,480
The way you two met

246
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:49,750
was too coincidental.

247
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:53,480
Even a screenwriter couldn't make it up.

248
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:02,390
It's been tough for Yimo.

249
00:13:03,270 --> 00:13:04,110
So I just

250
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:08,200
don't want her hurt again.

251
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:11,720
I worry she might feel unhappy.

252
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,910
So I've been checking in on her.

253
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,480
I grew up in a welfare home too.

254
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:22,910
So I can really relate.

255
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:25,240
You did?

256
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:28,630
Which one was it?

257
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,320
I wasn't there for long.

258
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,030
I was about that tall.

259
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,150
I don't remember much.

260
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:41,630
My master took me away.

261
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,510
And I just

262
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:45,000
grew up healthy, right?

263
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:58,790
Want anything else? We can order more.

264
00:13:58,790 --> 00:13:59,750
That's enough.

265
00:14:01,670 --> 00:14:02,510
Your beer.

266
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:07,630
Yimo, you ordered beer?

267
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:08,720
Ms. Tong,

268
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,550
can you drink?

269
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:12,960
Not really.

270
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:14,840
Two glasses and I'm tipsy.

271
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,270
I don't buy that.

272
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:18,670
You look like you can handle it.

273
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:20,600
I really can't.

274
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,480
Here. Have some meat.

275
00:14:21,510 --> 00:14:23,200
Come on, Ms. Tong.

276
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,480
My dad's not around.

277
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,630
It's just us.

278
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,550
He never lets me

279
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:29,510
drink outside alone.

280
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:30,720
Says it's not safe.

281
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,790
But you're here,

282
00:14:34,030 --> 00:14:35,360
so he can't say anything.

283
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:40,000
Alright. I'll drink with you.

284
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,200
How could you drink this much?

285
00:14:56,150 --> 00:14:57,000
And it's so late.

286
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:57,960
Really unsafe.

287
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,440
Don't do this again, okay?

288
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:04,390
Yimo,

289
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:06,630
if anything's wrong,

290
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:08,670
tell me.

291
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,510
You're a good kid.

292
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,600
Your dad's a good man.

293
00:15:14,630 --> 00:15:16,120
You're all good people.

294
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:21,360
If we could be one family,

295
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:23,080
that'd be even better.

296
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:29,720
Let me pull over.

297
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:41,990
Ms. Tong.

298
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,390
Just let it out.

299
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,840
Get her a bottle of water.

300
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:50,110
Ali,

301
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,080
trust me.

302
00:15:52,790 --> 00:15:54,750
I'll treat Yimo well.

303
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,840
Just like you do.

304
00:15:57,270 --> 00:15:58,790
Like my own daughter.

305
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,200
You're really drunk.

306
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,270
Ms. Tong, drink some water.

307
00:16:09,180 --> 00:16:12,460
(Qingcheng Public Security Bureau)

308
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,840
Li Xu's file. Take a look.

309
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:15,870
Can I have a sip?

310
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:20,540
(Personal File: Li Xu)

311
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,750
Master, I found something.

312
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:24,790
Back at the old teahouse,

313
00:16:24,790 --> 00:16:25,960
I felt something was off.

314
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:27,670
Li Xu

315
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,630
is one of the hidden investors there.

316
00:16:30,870 --> 00:16:33,030
And also in the dog shelter.

317
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:34,600
I've got a hunch

318
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:36,510
that he's playing a bigger role

319
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:38,030
behind the scenes.

320
00:16:38,510 --> 00:16:40,360
(Personal File: Li Xu)
I think we should

321
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,840
dig into him.

322
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:43,870
Li Xu needs checking.

323
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,670
But we still need the dog thieves.

324
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:48,110
Alright.

325
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,200
You've already narrowed that down.

326
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,150
Keep on it.

327
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:52,150
I'm on it.

328
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:54,120
However,

329
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:56,440
you've shown your face at the teahouse.

330
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:57,720
The round of checks.

331
00:16:59,510 --> 00:17:00,350
I'll handle it.

332
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:06,520
Captain Zhao.

333
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:08,350
I heard from Mr. Qin

334
00:17:08,510 --> 00:17:10,830
you chased a racer fugitive

335
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,200
for 80km back in the day

336
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,270
and forced him to stop.

337
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:17,830
All that old stuff.

338
00:17:17,830 --> 00:17:19,270
Only Qin still remembers.

339
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:22,030
With skills like yours,

340
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:24,070
why don't you drive yourself?

341
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:25,030
You brat.

342
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:27,720
What captain drives his own car?

343
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,510
What are you here for?

344
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,040
Me?

345
00:18:22,550 --> 00:18:23,400
Tea.

346
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:24,550
Tea?

347
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:27,750
You want it

348
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,510
light or strong?

349
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:32,240
What's the difference?

350
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:34,240
Big difference.

351
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:36,030
If you come during the day,

352
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:37,510
people usually go light.

353
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,070
But in the evening,

354
00:18:39,070 --> 00:18:40,350
they prefer it strong.

355
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,390
I see.

356
00:18:42,550 --> 00:18:45,030
I'll just have whatever.

357
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,510
Hello, what would you like?

358
00:18:57,550 --> 00:18:59,070
(Old Teahouse)
No prices listed here?

359
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:00,550
How much for Maojian?

360
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:01,960
Eighty one cup.

361
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,000
Eighty?

362
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,160
Scan here.

363
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,520
Bai.

364
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,350
You sure

365
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,110
your plan'll work?

366
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,040
Li,

367
00:19:19,830 --> 00:19:21,070
everything's set.

368
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,510
We're about to move.

369
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:24,790
What are you worried about?

370
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:27,640
Not worried.

371
00:19:28,590 --> 00:19:30,550
Just that guy you picked.

372
00:19:32,030 --> 00:19:33,350
I don't know him well.

373
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:35,350
Haven't worked together.

374
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:40,790
Sounds like you don't trust me.

375
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,240
That's not it.

376
00:19:44,110 --> 00:19:45,400
I mean,

377
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:48,920
if we're running a honey trap

378
00:19:49,070 --> 00:19:50,920
to lure rich suckers

379
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,790
and big shots,

380
00:19:52,590 --> 00:19:55,030
we don't need a real chef.

381
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:58,030
We got to use the best ingredients.

382
00:19:58,750 --> 00:19:59,590
Li,

383
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:02,920
we need a proper front.

384
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:05,000
No good chef,

385
00:20:06,110 --> 00:20:07,310
no bait.

386
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:18,400
Fine.

387
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,790
I won't interfere.

388
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:23,070
But let me be clear upfront,

389
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,750
if your guy

390
00:20:24,750 --> 00:20:26,400
screws up,

391
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,310
you're fully responsible.

392
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,190
Seven Character.

393
00:20:50,110 --> 00:20:51,350
Dad? You're home?

394
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:52,830
Not at the restaurant?

395
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,550
Everything's arranged.

396
00:20:56,350 --> 00:20:57,920
We're closing early tomorrow.

397
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,230
Taking the next two days off, too.

398
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,110
You've never

399
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,400
closed early

400
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,070
except for New Year's Eve.

401
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,240
What's so important?

402
00:21:09,270 --> 00:21:10,310
A banquet.

403
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,270
What kind?

404
00:21:15,550 --> 00:21:17,920
Client provides the venue.

405
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:19,790
We send the chef.

406
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:21,750
How's Li Tong?

407
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,200
She's fine.

408
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:24,400
Don't worry.

409
00:21:24,590 --> 00:21:25,480
But,

410
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:28,720
I realized I made a big mistake.

411
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:29,960
What's that?

412
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:31,750
Not inviting you along.

413
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:34,270
The three of us have never eaten together.

414
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:35,640
So,

415
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,310
I had an idea.

416
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:39,920
A crazy one?

417
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:44,270
I'm having dinner with Ms. Tong tonight.

418
00:21:44,270 --> 00:21:45,310
Come with us.

419
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:47,550
I booked a really nice place.

420
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,680
We can all have dinner

421
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,520
and chat.

422
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:51,750
I don't have time.

423
00:21:52,510 --> 00:21:55,110
You always say that.

424
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:56,790
I already booked it.

425
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:57,960
No refunds.

426
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:00,240
You wouldn't waste my money, right?

427
00:22:01,270 --> 00:22:02,350
Yimo...

428
00:22:02,350 --> 00:22:04,920
Dad, please.

429
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,590
Ms. Tong and I already agreed.

430
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:07,460
Please.

431
00:22:07,460 --> 00:22:09,160
Come with us.

432
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:19,030
I booked

433
00:22:19,030 --> 00:22:21,440
a really nice place for tonight.

434
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:22,720
I got my dad to come.

435
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,590
Dress nice, okay?

436
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:28,260
(Yimo)

437
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:30,340
(Goes as planned)

438
00:22:36,830 --> 00:22:38,110
Tea lovers,

439
00:22:38,550 --> 00:22:41,640
I'm at a new spot today.

440
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,960
Check out the place.

441
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,070
Look, a rickshaw.

442
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,030
Nice. Very old-fashioned.

443
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,440
There's even a rooster.

444
00:22:53,590 --> 00:22:57,070
Must be a historic building.

445
00:22:59,590 --> 00:23:01,000
Oh, an old gate.

446
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:02,560
Great.

447
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:04,680
Nice vibe,

448
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,030
actually.

449
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,240
Your Maojian. Receipt.

450
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,830
Thanks.

451
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:34,550
Add more tea.

452
00:23:35,030 --> 00:23:37,310
Extra tea's 20. Want it?

453
00:23:40,070 --> 00:23:41,200
What are you doing?

454
00:23:42,550 --> 00:23:43,790
What are you doing?

455
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:44,960
You call this Maojian?

456
00:23:45,110 --> 00:23:45,950
It is.

457
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:47,310
Maojian's green tea.

458
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,480
But you served me red.

459
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:50,410
Sir,

460
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,400
you didn't say

461
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,350
red or green when you ordered.

462
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:55,070
Why are you mad now?

463
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,480
Of course I'm mad.

464
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:58,960
I heard this place was classy.

465
00:23:59,350 --> 00:24:01,160
Good views, good tea.

466
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,720
I came to enjoy myself.

467
00:24:02,830 --> 00:24:04,110
You serve me this?

468
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:06,310
Think I can't afford better?

469
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,590
Well, sir,

470
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,200
it's not at this hour.

471
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:11,400
During daytime,

472
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,350
the tea's all like this.

473
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:13,190
What do you mean?

474
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,440
Did I come at the wrong time?

475
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,310
Night tea's much better?

476
00:24:19,070 --> 00:24:21,270
Guaranteed.

477
00:24:21,590 --> 00:24:22,720
But you know,

478
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,400
it's a bit more pricey.

479
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:25,920
Price doesn't matter.

480
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,680
My pension's high.

481
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,830
Please have some tea first.

482
00:24:28,830 --> 00:24:30,070
Let me get you a fresh pot.

483
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:31,300
- Go on.
- Yes, sir.

484
00:25:17,740 --> 00:25:21,420
(Community Service Center)

485
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:26,480
Officer,

486
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:29,160
here's the rental list.

487
00:25:29,310 --> 00:25:31,480
The info you asked is in here.

488
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,750
Thanks. You carry on.

489
00:25:32,830 --> 00:25:33,670
Sure.

490
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:40,820
(Rental Tenant Registry)

491
00:25:40,820 --> 00:25:45,620
(Zhang Junlong; Wang Hu)

492
00:25:49,660 --> 00:25:52,900
(Qingcheng Public Security Bureau)

493
00:26:07,270 --> 00:26:08,270
What's up, old man?

494
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,960
Had a spending spree?

495
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:14,480
You ordered an 80-a-cup tea?

496
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,200
Didn't that hurt when you paid?

497
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:18,440
Work-related. I'll get reimbursed.

498
00:26:18,830 --> 00:26:20,110
I'm not paying out of pocket.

499
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:21,240
Well,

500
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:24,640
after that cup,

501
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:25,640
can you still drink

502
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,550
a five-yuan pack?

503
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:28,680
It's fake. Not real Maojian.

504
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:30,830
You could tell?

505
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,510
I don't buy it often

506
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:33,680
doesn't mean I don't know tea.

507
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,110
Fake tea.

508
00:26:36,790 --> 00:26:38,000
Fake teahouse too.

509
00:26:40,030 --> 00:26:40,880
I need

510
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:43,830
to dig a little deeper on Li Xu.

511
00:26:44,750 --> 00:26:47,270
I just went

512
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,960
over the dog thieves' info again.

513
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:52,350
Turns out they're pretty interesting.

514
00:26:52,790 --> 00:26:54,510
Lately they've been all over the place.

515
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,350
And I think they're not too bright.

516
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:00,720
Doesn't feel like

517
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:03,310
they could plan that many thefts.

518
00:27:05,070 --> 00:27:06,550
And I keep thinking

519
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,680
they're somehow connected

520
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:11,960
to Hongyun Restaurant.

521
00:27:13,880 --> 00:27:15,000
If you suspect it,

522
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,000
find evidence

523
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:18,720
to prove it.

524
00:27:23,830 --> 00:27:26,400
So I'm not forcing connections now?

525
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:30,960
What's that supposed to mean?

526
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:32,480
Recognition.

527
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:35,270
Then say it.

528
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,400
Why do you

529
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,750
always talk in riddles?

530
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:41,480
You stubbornness and little mind games.

531
00:27:41,790 --> 00:27:43,030
Straight talk's boring.

532
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:44,400
If you won't say it straight,

533
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:46,110
neither will I.

534
00:27:47,590 --> 00:27:48,590
Anyway,

535
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:51,750
someone's been acting different lately.

536
00:27:51,750 --> 00:27:53,270
Don't copy my tricks.

537
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:55,030
What are you hinting at?

538
00:27:57,030 --> 00:27:58,640
Funny how some grumpy old guy

539
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,240
was dead-set

540
00:28:01,550 --> 00:28:03,510
against this case a while ago.

541
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:07,160
Now his eyes light up

542
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,590
when he works it.

543
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:12,680
Master,

544
00:28:13,750 --> 00:28:15,400
can you tell me

545
00:28:15,790 --> 00:28:17,510
why you didn't

546
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:19,030
want this case back then?

547
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,590
We're at this point now,

548
00:28:25,590 --> 00:28:26,960
please just tell me.

549
00:28:29,510 --> 00:28:32,270
Is the Nude Banquet Case

550
00:28:33,030 --> 00:28:34,400
connected to the welfare home

551
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,160
I grew up in?

552
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,000
Yes.

553
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,750
Back then, we realized

554
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:50,270
the banquet

555
00:28:50,750 --> 00:28:52,030
happened more than once.

556
00:28:52,260 --> 00:28:53,310
The time it all went wrong,

557
00:28:55,310 --> 00:28:56,880
those kids

558
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:01,960
were from

559
00:29:02,510 --> 00:29:04,240
the welfare home you lived in.

560
00:29:05,830 --> 00:29:06,670
Captain.

561
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:08,000
We can't call off the task force.

562
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,680
We can't just shelve this case.

563
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:11,720
No new leads.

564
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,830
We can't put all our manpower on this.

565
00:29:14,110 --> 00:29:15,480
Other cases are piling up.

566
00:29:15,590 --> 00:29:17,880
Give me more time.

567
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:18,720
I'll keep digging.

568
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:19,960
There will be leads.

569
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,400
It's not that I won't give you time.

570
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:23,310
Zhao Fengcheng, listen.

571
00:29:23,480 --> 00:29:25,590
You're not working just one case.

572
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:27,110
Cases are piling up.

573
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:29,790
- Captain.
- If you keep burning yourself on this,

574
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,720
you'll be drained.

575
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:32,680
You get that?

576
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:33,790
No, Cap...

577
00:29:45,020 --> 00:29:47,460
(Captain)

578
00:29:53,510 --> 00:29:54,720
The welfare home was shut down.

579
00:29:55,750 --> 00:29:56,880
The kids

580
00:29:57,270 --> 00:29:58,830
were sent for adoption

581
00:29:59,110 --> 00:30:01,400
or transferred.

582
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:02,390
You know,

583
00:30:02,790 --> 00:30:03,790
Tang Tang was there too.

584
00:30:04,030 --> 00:30:05,880
Tang Zhigang was your buddy.

585
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:07,310
Would you

586
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,270
look after his son?

587
00:30:13,270 --> 00:30:14,110
I...

588
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:18,270
I'm not fit to raise a kid.

589
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:19,960
Zhao Fengcheng,

590
00:30:20,510 --> 00:30:22,510
don't forget you're a detective.

591
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,000
You have to adjust

592
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,400
and move on.

593
00:30:26,550 --> 00:30:27,920
The case is shelved,

594
00:30:28,030 --> 00:30:29,310
not dead.

595
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:31,030
I believe that one day,

596
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:32,480
we'll crack it.

597
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,270
Even if we can't,

598
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,440
the younger ones will.

599
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,640
The next generation will.

600
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:42,150
Come.

601
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,920
Had I not been so lost back then,

602
00:31:03,510 --> 00:31:04,960
I should've adopted you.

603
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:06,790
You wouldn't have ended up there.

604
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:10,350
After the case,

605
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:12,200
I got scared.

606
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:14,750
So I took you out.

607
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,040
But now,

608
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:19,270
the case's reopened.

609
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:21,310
It's not I'm against it.

610
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:22,720
It's just...

611
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,480
I don't want you dragged into it.

612
00:31:45,780 --> 00:31:46,670
What's wrong with you?

613
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:51,200
What's with the low spirit?

614
00:31:51,270 --> 00:31:53,310
You look like a rookie.

615
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,030
Look at me.

616
00:31:55,590 --> 00:31:56,590
Young,

617
00:31:56,790 --> 00:31:57,750
brilliant,

618
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:59,240
and full of promise.

619
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,070
Who trained me?

620
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:02,880
You did.

621
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:12,550
Where'd you learn that thick skin?

622
00:32:17,070 --> 00:32:19,030
From you, who else?

623
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,310
That's better.

624
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:28,720
Yell at me once in a while.

625
00:32:28,830 --> 00:32:30,680
That makes me feel better.

626
00:32:34,550 --> 00:32:35,400
Master,

627
00:32:37,310 --> 00:32:38,720
I found Huahua.

628
00:32:39,030 --> 00:32:41,070
My friend at the welfare home

629
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:42,750
who went missing.

630
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:45,550
I found her.

631
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:47,070
You did?

632
00:32:48,070 --> 00:32:48,910
Yes.

633
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:50,480
Not just that.

634
00:32:52,350 --> 00:32:53,310
I also found out

635
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:55,310
why she disappeared

636
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:59,200
and why she forgot everything at the time.

637
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:02,720
How did you find her?

638
00:33:03,110 --> 00:33:03,950
Who is it?

639
00:33:05,830 --> 00:33:06,750
Wang Yimo.

640
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:10,590
You're sure?

641
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:12,840
Absolutely.

642
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:17,160
You know what I felt

643
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:19,510
after I knew?

644
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:23,800
Regret.

645
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:31,510
Even though I was a kid,

646
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:34,070
why didn't I

647
00:33:34,070 --> 00:33:35,880
stand up back then?

648
00:33:38,310 --> 00:33:39,510
If I had,

649
00:33:39,510 --> 00:33:41,640
maybe things would've been different.

650
00:33:43,270 --> 00:33:45,110
She wouldn't have

651
00:33:45,110 --> 00:33:46,720
gone through that.

652
00:33:49,350 --> 00:33:50,830
She wouldn't have

653
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,640
forgotten everything.

654
00:33:57,110 --> 00:33:58,550
You were just a kid too.

655
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:01,480
Nothing you could do.

656
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:12,400
But now I'm not.

657
00:34:16,070 --> 00:34:18,000
I've got this case now.

658
00:34:18,510 --> 00:34:20,230
I'll see it through.

659
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:23,110
I'm not that clueless kid anymore.

660
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:25,630
Though I'm still a bit green.

661
00:34:26,190 --> 00:34:27,880
I'll give it everything I've got.

662
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:33,230
I'm gonna reel in every last one

663
00:34:33,230 --> 00:34:34,440
of those scumbags

664
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:35,670
from that case.

665
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:39,600
I'll fulfill

666
00:34:40,110 --> 00:34:41,150
your long-held wish.

667
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:44,510
And for the victims,

668
00:34:45,110 --> 00:34:46,110
including Huahua,

669
00:34:47,320 --> 00:34:48,360
I'll see justice done.

670
00:34:53,190 --> 00:34:54,070
Boss,

671
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:59,070
is there really no other way?

672
00:34:59,710 --> 00:35:00,670
What are you saying?

673
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:03,720
Ali,

674
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:06,190
all these years,

675
00:35:06,190 --> 00:35:08,000
we've been keeping our heads down.

676
00:35:08,630 --> 00:35:09,960
If we take this job,

677
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,320
we're back in the mud.

678
00:35:15,510 --> 00:35:16,670
I've said all I need to.

679
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:18,640
Get to work.

680
00:35:55,510 --> 00:35:56,350
Coming.

681
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:58,320
Let's go.

682
00:36:00,510 --> 00:36:01,350
Stop drinking.

683
00:36:42,590 --> 00:36:43,670
We're not late.

684
00:36:43,670 --> 00:36:44,760
Still got time.

685
00:36:46,710 --> 00:36:47,550
Dad,

686
00:36:47,670 --> 00:36:49,480
we can't go empty-handed.

687
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,230
What do you mean?

688
00:36:53,070 --> 00:36:53,910
Come with me.

689
00:37:15,150 --> 00:37:15,990
Please enjoy.

690
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:16,840
Thanks.

691
00:37:31,190 --> 00:37:32,440
Dad, hurry up.

692
00:37:37,550 --> 00:37:38,390
What's wrong?

693
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:42,400
Let's go inside.

694
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:43,350
Sure.

695
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:46,600
Ms. Tong.

696
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:48,120
You're here.

697
00:37:48,510 --> 00:37:49,840
These are from my dad.

698
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:52,800
Traffic?

699
00:37:53,150 --> 00:37:54,030
A bit.

700
00:37:54,030 --> 00:37:55,360
Good thing we left early.

701
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:59,800
I saw someone talking to you.

702
00:38:00,150 --> 00:38:00,990
Who was it?

703
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:04,360
Wrong table.

704
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:09,280
Is this for three?

705
00:38:09,350 --> 00:38:10,190
Two.

706
00:38:10,190 --> 00:38:11,590
Dinner's already arranged.

707
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:12,800
Alright.

708
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:15,630
My job's done.

709
00:38:16,070 --> 00:38:18,360
I'll leave you two to it.

710
00:38:18,550 --> 00:38:20,400
Have a lovely night.

711
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:21,320
I'm heading out.

712
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:28,590
This feels like a TV show.

713
00:39:14,220 --> 00:39:15,980
(Wang Li was at the restaurant today.
Wang Li had a business dinner.)

714
00:39:15,980 --> 00:39:18,020
(He stayed home today.)

715
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:18,860
(No text for days.
He hasn't been at the restaurant.)

716
00:39:18,860 --> 00:39:19,700
(On a business trip. Back tomorrow.
Didn't find out what for.)

717
00:39:19,700 --> 00:39:20,540
(Be sharp; His daughter's back.
Got it.)

718
00:39:39,370 --> 00:39:44,860
♪Dreams of the past sleep in the chill♪

719
00:39:44,860 --> 00:39:48,310
♪Now I run toward the light♪

720
00:39:50,160 --> 00:39:55,420
♪What does the fire burn,
what does it reveal?♪

721
00:39:55,740 --> 00:39:59,390
♪Is the answer found when the sun rises♪

722
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:04,290
♪If it's all a lie♪

723
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:09,650
♪Should I tear it open?♪

724
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:15,700
♪If it's all part of the journey♪

725
00:40:16,380 --> 00:40:21,230
♪Then face the blaze head-on♪

726
00:40:21,620 --> 00:40:26,090
♪Let the sun awaken my heart's crave♪

727
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:32,360
♪Pain reminds me I'm alive♪

728
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:37,290
♪The world can't take away every clear sky♪

729
00:40:37,940 --> 00:40:43,090
♪The hotter it gets, the fiercer I fight♪

730
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:48,120
♪Let the sun burn away all I lean upon♪

731
00:40:48,460 --> 00:40:54,120
♪Leave me only what endures♪

732
00:40:54,230 --> 00:40:59,780
♪At the cliff's edge, all fear shatters♪

733
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:06,790
♪With a grounded heart, a soul like fire♪
